
"Fine then! Go date the hoe in that picture! I don't give a shit," I screamed back, my voice uneven as the words left my dry mouth.
"I will," He said, quieter this time. The smallest tear slid down his face, our eyes locked.
"Goodbye," I whispered, looking at my hands. I could feel him stare at me through the camera of his laptop, me being too scared to look up.
He ended the session, leaving the window on my screen black and me empty.
"I love you."
